"{\"uid\": \"rappler.com-sports-filipino-olympians-serve-paris-2024-looks\", \"text\": \"  SUMMARY  This is AI generated summarization, which may have errors. For context, always refer to the full article.  OLYMPIC READY. Several members of Team Philippines gear up for the Paris Olympics.  adidas  MANILA, Philippines - Filipino Olympians showed they are ready to serve looks as well as winning performances in the 2024 Paris Olympics.  Just weeks before Team Philippines leaves for Metz, France for a month-longtraining camp, some of the country's elite athletes showcased their team wear, with adidas as the national team's official outfitter.  \\\"We look forward to seeing Filipino athletes raise the flag on the global stage together with our partners who share the same vision,\\\" said Philippine Olympic Committee (POC) president Bambol Tolentino as the country marks its 100th year of participation in the Olympics.  Anthony Frangos, country manager of adidas Philippines, said the brand aims to \\\"invest in the future of Philippine sports\\\" as it partners with the POC.  \\\"The Olympics is a global sporting moment that truly highlights the incredible breadth and variety of sport, and our mission is to help Filipino athletes shine under pressure,\\\" said Frangos.  \\\"Our sleek, modern designs are inspired by the national spirit, aiming to connect athletes to their roots while enabling them to perform at their very best,\\\" he added as adidas provides the Olympic Village and podium looks of all Filipino athletes in Paris.  As a several more athletes vie to qualify, 15 Filipinos already earned theirParis Olympics spotsas of June 12.  They are expected to leave for the Metz training camp late June, before the Paris Games kick off on July 26.  - Rappler.com  How does this make you feel?  follow us          \"}"